description:
The A.P.N.G. stands together as Sly threatens to destroy everything they hold dear. Will the A.P.N.G., now at full strength, be able to stop Sly here on Zadaar – 3 and prevent him from getting to NEW-GEN?

Mini has been joined by the rest of the A.P.N.G., in Diamond, Flyer, Gazelle, and Roboduck.

The battle is fast and dangerous with the A.P.N.G. now together putting a major hurt and dent on Sly’s operation and Microbots.

Back on NEW-GEN, Gabriel has used his Kane to create an emblem for the A.P.N.G. that will create a new device for them to use in battle. The nanoglove.

Sly, who realizes he is slowly losing the battle, retreats to the city of Zadaar-3 to create something more powerful using their technology to defeat the A.P.N.G.

Chris and Sean on Earth find themselves sick, as their bodies are begin the final stages of changes that will allow them access to their powers. Gabriel and Thea realize that their twins need them, but Gabriel has to deal with the situation at hand.

The A.P.N.G. is resting, having dealt with the vast majority of Sly’s forces when they suddenly see a force rushing at them from a distance. Realizing the battle isn’t over, the A.P.N.G. prepare to fight once more.

This is the final issue of the first mini series. The A.P.N.G. stands ready to face off one on one with Sly as he prepares to attack them with all his robots and powers.

Sean’s nightmares start the issue, with visions of Sly and Metalmites chasing he and Chris down alleyways. He awakens in a sweat, comforted by his brother, as his parents watch from the hallway, realizing the time is drawing ever closer to their powers developing.

On Zaadar-3. the A.P.N.G. begins their attack on Sly’s horde of machines as they continue to grow bigger and stronger. They do well until the individual parts they are destroying begin to reform together and become a colossal new creature which grabs hold of all of them. At this point Sly enters the battle attacking them.

He attacks them with an electromagnetic surge which causes their nanos to deactivate suddenly, painfully reverting them back to their human forms. Sly continues to press the attack, pounding on them, leaving Roboduck the only one able to fight until he is quickly taken out of the battle.

As Sly prepares to land the killing blow on the members of the A.P.N.G., Gabriel appears in a blinding flash ready for battle. He releases his new invention of the nanoglove, which quickly affixes itself to the members of the A.P.N.G., giving them back their abilities and getting them back into the fight.

Sly and Gabriel begin to battle high above them, both throwing energy blasts, machines and hand to hand blows at one another.

The A.P.N.G. below uses the power of their nanogloves to take out the monstrous creature that Sly created that previously had taken them down.

Gabriel and Sly continue to fight high above and in the end Gabriel uses the nanobots in his body as a weapon, sending them out from inside him and using them to finally defeat Sly, and send him back to the Underworld.

Sly has arrived and has begun his attack on the world of Zaadar-3.   His MetalMites and Microbots quickly go to work attacking the inhabitants of the world, making short work of their cities and defenses.

Meanwhile on NEW-GEN, Gabriel and Thea confer over the development of the students, while on Earth, Sean continues to have nightmares of MetalMites as their powers continue to develop.

Gabriel learns of Sly’s incursion to Zaadar-3 and sends Mini in to evaluate the situation. The situation quickly devolves into a fight with Mini trying to fight off nearly a planet of Sly’s creations.

At his bleakest moment, Mini is rescued by the arrival of the rest of the A.P.N.G. who have now joined the fight.

Over the past three years, he's faced New Ways to Die, a Gauntlet, and a Grim Hunt, and, through it all, Spider-Man has stood stronger than ever. But while recent events may have drastically changed Peter and his friends, the ol' Parker luck threatens a turn for the even-worse at any second. One thing's for certain though, the sun is setting on the Wallcrawler's Brand New Day, and tomorrow begins right here!

description: THE END OF THE MARVEL UNIVERSE IS NIGH! As the penultimate step in the destruction of all creation, the CHAOS KING’S annihilating army of slave gods -- including an undead (and angry) ARES, GOD OF WAR -- takes on every divine pantheon on this mudball called Earth! Can Thor, Allfather Hercules and the God Squad rally Earth's feuding gods to beat back their common enemy and save existence itself? Or will a shocking betrayal pave the way for the triumph of chaos and darkness? More epic, divine madness from New York Times Bestselling "Incredible Hercules" writers Greg Pak and Fred Van Lente and fan-favorite penciler Khoi Pham! P.S: what a horrible glitch in the cover: 3 of 4!!

description:
Fan-favorite anti-hero Taskmaster and his thoroughly involuntary sidekick/love interest Mercedes Merced are on the precipice of unlocking Tasky's secret origin, which is so secret even he doesn't know what it is. The final leg of the journey involves storming a foreboding Bavarian castle ... high in the South American Andes? And if that wasn't bizarre enough, Taskmaster finds goose-stepping Seig-Heiling death in "THE TOWN WHERE EVERYONE IS HITLER". Guest-Starring Nick Fury and Steve Rogers, Super-Soldier.

description:
The dark underworld of espionage and crime is lit up by the fatal charms of the gorgeous Modesty Blaise — high priestess of pulp crime and goddess of cult thrillers!

In this latest volume, Modesty faces off against a group of racketeers who have eyes on valuable Native American treasure in ‘Yellowstone Booty'; in ‘Idaho George', Modesty and a con man are imprisoned by a gang who want to turn fools gold into the real thing; and in ‘The Golden Frog', learn about the secret origin of her fighting skills!

Featuring brand new story introductions by Modesty creator and bestselling author Peter O'Donnell, plus exclusive behind-the-scenes paintings and rarely seen artwork by John Burns, this latest addition to the Modesty Blaise library is not to be missed!
name: Yellowstone Booty

description: Dorothy Gale plunges into adventure again, this time with a talking chicken named Billina. Dorothy and Billina are washed off their sailing ship to face drowning, starvation, and screaming Wheelers, strange men with wheels instead of hands and feet. The multiple Eisner Award-winning and New York Times bestselling team of Shanower and Young returns to Oz with this comics adaptation of L. Frank Baum’s third Oz book.

There was a year when no one knew where he was. When Bullseye – the world’s greatest assassin – simply vanished without a trace. In the glare of the white hot lights, no one noticed the lanky stranger with the rubber arm, throwing heat that could, well, take off a man’s head. See, every man needs a challenge, a moment when he faces impossible odds, when he looks deep inside himself and sees what he’s really made of. Bullseye’s next pitch is one for the history books.

Beginning a five-issue mini-series chronicling the rebirth of Captain America! When the Avengers pull a mysterious, tattered soldier from the sea, they unwittingly bring back to life the Living Legend of World War Two--a man whose memories of a life sixty years ago are as fresh as yesterday! How will Steve Rogers, frozen in suspended animation for half a century, adapt to the world of the 21st century?

description: The critically acclaimed limited series comes to an end. The mystery of this Stone Age world is revealed, and the Deviants – having their unity tested on literal fields of battle – face a challenge that no sane person could expect them to pass. Second chances don't come around often, and one member won't receive one…

description: Those barely legal girls are back again in two ball-busting stories. This issue features the stories of two sisters. Big sister teaches little sister in the ways of "pet training," but rolling over and sitting up were not quite like this. The second story takes place at an isolated ice cream stand where big sister shows her trainee the real meaning of "gooey treats." All of this and more in FULL-COLOR!

"Last Gleaming," part 3 of 5. While Super Buffy is fighting side by side with Spike in Sunnydale, Angel is on the other side of the world fighting demons of his own. As Twilight he was given a clear mission in regard to Buffy--help her reach the next plane, together create a new world, and end all suffering. But Buffy doesn't play by the rules, and this "higher plane" and a lifetime of happiness with Angel wasn't gonna cut it--not if she had to sacrifice her family to keep it. And now Angel has to answer for his failings as Twilight--willingly or not.
name: Last Gleaming, Part Three

description: The Cavalier – that's the Z-lister with the swords, right? So how'd he manage to frame Catwoman for a run of burglaries? And how on Earth did he manage the more spectacular crime of cleaning out the Wayne Enterprises pension fund and framing Bruce Wayne for the deed? However impressive he may appear to be, The Cavalier will quickly learn that frame-ups like that cut both ways, as both Batman and Catwoman begin tracking the Gotham City villain in this stand-alone one-shot from comics legend Howard Chaykin!
